sition: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">440</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":440,\"repo\":\"PistonDevelopers/glfw-rs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> — <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/PistonDevelopers/glfw-rs\"><img src=\"https://api.travis-ci.org/PistonDevelopers/glfw-rs.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"build badge\"></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/glutin\">glutin</a> — Rust alternative to <a href=\"https://www.glfw.org/\">GLFW</a> <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/rust-windowing/glutin\"><img src=\"https://api.travis-ci.org/rust-windowing/glutin.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"build badge\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-27T14:08:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Systems</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~213/\">15-213</a> <strong>Introduction to Computer Systems (ICS)</strong> <em>Carnegie-Mellon University</em>  <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4f9.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Videos\" title=\"Lecture Videos\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>The ICS course provides a programmer's view of how computer systems execute programs, store information, and communicate. It enables students to become more effective programmers, especially in dealing with issues of performance, portability and robustness. It also serves as a foundation for courses on compilers, networks, operating systems, and computer architecture, where a deeper understanding of systems-level issues is required. Topics covered include: machine-level code and its generation by optimizing compilers, performance evaluation and optimization, computer arithmetic, memory organization and management, networking technology and protocols, and supporting concurrent computation.</li>\n<li>This is the must-have course for everyone in CMU who wants to learn some computer science no matter what major are you in. Because it's CMU (The course number is as same as the zip code of CMU)!</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~213/schedule.html\">Lecture Notes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scs.hosted.panopto.com/Panopto/Pages/Sessions/List.aspx#folderID=%22b96d90ae-9871-4fae-91e2-b1627b43e25e%22\">Videos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://csapp.cs.cmu.edu/public/labs.html\">Assignments</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-27T13:18:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Misc</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.stanford.edu/class/cs193a/lectures.shtml\">CS 193a</a> <strong>Android App Development, Spring 2016</strong> <em>Stanford University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4f9.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Videos\" title=\"Lecture Videos\"><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>Course Description: This course provides an introduction to developing applications for the Android mobile platform.</li>\n<li>Prerequisite: CS 106B or equivalent. Java experience highly recommended. OOP highly recommmended.</li>\n<li>Devices: Access to an Android phone and/or tablet recommended but not required.</li>\n<li>Videos: Videos list can be found <a href=\"http://web.stanford.edu/class/cs193a/videos.shtml\">here</a></li>\n<li>Other materials: Some codes, handsout, homework ..... and lecture notes are not downloadable on the site due to login requirement. Please head to my Github repo <a href=\"https://github.com/VoLuong/Materials-CS193A-Android-App-Development-Standford\">here</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/VoLuong/Materials-CS193A-Android-App-Development-Standford\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">106</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":106,\"repo\":\"VoLuong/Materials-CS193A-Android-App-Development-Standford\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> to download them.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-27T13:18:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphic Displays</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GuangchuangYu/ggtree\">ggtree</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GuangchuangYu/ggtree\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">518</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":518,\"repo\":\"GuangchuangYu/ggtree\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Visualization and annotation of phylogenetic tree.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-27T12:22:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"0xnr/awesome-bigdata","categoryHTML":"<h2>Time-Series Databases</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kairosdb/kairosdb\">Kairosdb</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kairosdb/kairosdb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1600,\"repo\":\"kairosdb/kairosdb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - similar to OpenTSDB but allows for Cassandra.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-27T11:32:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"quozd/awesome-dotnet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Documentation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/EWSoftware/SHFB\">Sandcastle</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/EWSoftware/SHFB\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;backgrou